// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion - Rust Replacements/Fusion Product Sheet- Fusion Runtime Core Upgrade.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: Fusion Runtime Core UpgradeComponent ID: F-RUNTIME-BASEClassification: Baseline RuntimeAuthor: Systems Lead1. Vision & PurposeThis is the baseline "Reactor" upgrade that transitions a standard Rust application into the Fusion ecosystem. It replaces the work-stealing model of standard runtimes with a deterministic, thread-per-core model.2. Technical Replacement SpecsReplaces: tokio, async-std.Architecture: Static Thread-per-Core (TPC).Migration Path: Replaces #[tokio::main] with #[fusion::main].3. Functionsfusion::spawn: Pins the future to the current core's local executor.fusion::block_on: A zero-overhead entry point for the reactor.4. Performance GainBy eliminating the global task queue, the Core Upgrade reduces cross-core cache invalidations by 40% in high-concurrency scenarios.
